root_cause: CONFIRMED. User blended land cover x hillshade on Chattanooga -> output GREYSCALE instead of colored-landcover-with-shadows. The land cover COG is a SINGLE-BAND NLCD palette-INDEX raster; its colors live in an EMBEDDED GDAL color table (TiTiler colorizes from it at display; the published tile has no explicit colormap). compute_blended_composite._read_base_rgb (compute_blended_composite.py ~L210-213) BROADCASTS a single-band base to grayscale (R=G=B) -> the palette colors never applied before the multiply -> grayscale shaded relief.
